                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.03,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 146620,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has the opinion of the Court this morning in case 08-598, Bobby verus Bies."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.03,
                        "stop": 313.896,
                        "byte_start": 146620,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.03,
                                "stop": 23.51,
                                "byte_start": 146620,
                                "byte_stop": 200537,
                                "text": "In Atkins v. Virginia, decided in 2002, this Court held that the Eighth Amendment bars execution of mentally retarded offenders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.51,
                                "stop": 36.983,
                                "byte_start": 200537,
                                "byte_stop": 254454,
                                "text": "Under our pre-Atkins precedent, mental retardation, narrative consideration as a mitigating factor but did not bar in position of the death penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.983,
                                "stop": 51.014,
                                "byte_start": 254454,
                                "byte_stop": 310565,
                                "text": "Nearly, a decade before Atkins, respondent Michael Bies was tried and convicted in Ohio of the aggravated murder, kidnapping and attempted rape of a 10-year-old boy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.014,
                                "stop": 70.332,
                                "byte_start": 310565,
                                "byte_stop": 387887,
                                "text": "At the sentencing stage, the trial judge instructed the jury to weigh mitigating circumstances including evidence of Bies\u0027 mile to borderline mental retardation against aggravating circumstances including the crime\u0027s brutality."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.332,
                                "stop": 75.817,
                                "byte_start": 387887,
                                "byte_stop": 409830,
                                "text": "The jury recommended a death sentence which the trial court imposed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.817,
                                "stop": 91.909,
                                "byte_start": 409830,
                                "byte_stop": 474196,
                                "text": "Ohio\u0027s Court of Appeals and the Supreme Court affirmed, each concluding that Bies\u0027 mental retardation was entitled to someway in litigation, but that the aggravators outweighed the mitigators."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.909,
                                "stop": 104.236,
                                "byte_start": 474196,
                                "byte_stop": 523515,
                                "text": "After this Court decided Atkins, Bies sought state post conviction relief and the Court ordered a full hearing on Bies\u0027 mental capacity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.236,
                                "stop": 119.849,
                                "byte_start": 523515,
                                "byte_stop": 585895,
                                "text": "Rather than proceeding with that hearing, Bies filed a federal habeas petition in U.S. District Court, contending that the Fifth Amendments\u0027 Double Jeopardy Clause barred the State from re-litigating the issue of his mental retardation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.849,
                                "stop": 126.571,
                                "byte_start": 585895,
                                "byte_stop": 612854,
                                "text": "The District Court granted the habeas petition and the Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.571,
                                "stop": 134.093,
                                "byte_start": 612854,
                                "byte_stop": 642947,
                                "text": "The Sixth Circuit identified as the controlling precedent this Court\u0027s decision in Ashe v. Swenson."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.093,
                                "stop": 141.079,
                                "byte_start": 642947,
                                "byte_stop": 670845,
                                "text": "We held in Ashe that the doctrine of issue preclusion is a component of the Double Jeopardy Clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.079,
                                "stop": 153.389,
                                "byte_start": 670845,
                                "byte_stop": 720060,
                                "text": "Issue preclusion was dispositive of Bies\u0027 case as Sixth Circuit believed of critical importance to its decision, the Sixth Circuit found necessary to the death penalty sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.389,
                                "stop": 160.096,
                                "byte_start": 720060,
                                "byte_stop": 746914,
                                "text": "The Ohio Court\u0027s recognition that Bies is qualified as mentally retarded."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.096,
                                "stop": 166.887,
                                "byte_start": 746914,
                                "byte_stop": 774081,
                                "text": "We reverse and note first that Bies was not twice put in jeopardy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.887,
                                "stop": 187.091,
                                "byte_start": 774081,
                                "byte_stop": 854956,
                                "text": "He was convicted and sentenced to death and Ohio sought no further prosecution or punishment rather, rather than successive efforts to prosecute or punish him, this case involves successive efforts by Bies to overturn his capital sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.091,
                                "stop": 201.931,
                                "byte_start": 854956,
                                "byte_stop": 914307,
                                "text": "The doctrine of issue preclusion on which the Sixth Circuit relied, bars litigation of issues actually determined and necessary to the ultimate outcome of a prior proceeding."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.931,
                                "stop": 208.674,
                                "byte_start": 914307,
                                "byte_stop": 941265,
                                "text": "The Federal Court of Appeals held that all requirements with issue preclusion were met in Bies\u0027 case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.674,
                                "stop": 220.305,
                                "byte_start": 941265,
                                "byte_stop": 987763,
                                "text": "That holding was in correct because mental retardation was not a conclusive or necessary determination in any Ohio court proceeding to date."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.305,
                                "stop": 226.634,
                                "byte_start": 987763,
                                "byte_stop": 1013049,
                                "text": "The determination ranks as necessary, only when the final outcome hinges on it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 226.634,
                                "stop": 240.197,
                                "byte_start": 1013049,
                                "byte_stop": 1067384,
                                "text": "Statements made by the Ohio Courts regarding Bies\u0027 mental capacity, plainly worth not necessary to the final outcome that is the judgment affirming his death sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.197,
                                "stop": 252.599,
                                "byte_start": 1067384,
                                "byte_stop": 1116912,
                                "text": "Further, even if court issue preclusion requirements had been met, an exemption to the doctrine\u0027s application would be warranted due to the intervening Atkins decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 252.599,
                                "stop": 261.603,
                                "byte_start": 1116912,
                                "byte_stop": 1152961,
                                "text": "That change in law substantially alters the State\u0027s incentive to contest Bies\u0027 mental capacity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 261.603,
                                "stop": 265.981,
                                "byte_start": 1152961,
                                "byte_stop": 1170516,
                                "text": "Under Atkins, mental retardation bars a death sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.981,
                                "stop": 277.567,
                                "byte_start": 1170516,
                                "byte_stop": 1216805,
                                "text": "When Bies was tried however, retardation was only a mitigator, moreover of retardation play, pre-Atkins could backfire."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 277.567,
                                "stop": 289.415,
                                "byte_start": 1216805,
                                "byte_stop": 1264243,
                                "text": "The prosecutor could seize an evidence of the defendant\u0027s diminished capacity to urge the defendant\u0027s dangerousness to others, rendering death, not like the appropriate sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 289.415,
                                "stop": 303.115,
                                "byte_start": 1264243,
                                "byte_stop": 1318996,
                                "text": "In short, the question whether Bies qualifies under Atkins as a mentally retarded person, ineligible for the death penalty is now right for a foreign fair determination in State Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 303.115,
                                "stop": 313.896,
                                "byte_start": 1318996,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our decision corrects the Federal Court\u0027s errors in temporarily derailing that determination, the opinion of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
